channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Famed beach vanishes as wild storms hit
item.description: Byron Bay’s Main Beach has been washed away as wild weather batters the coast.

item.title: Man dies after stabbing police dog
item.description: A man has died and a police dog is in a serious condition after an alleged break-and-enter turned violent in southeast Queensland overnight.

item.title: Drink-driver’s shocking alcohol reading
item.description: A South Australian man has lost his licence after allegedly being caught seven times over the legal alcohol limit.

item.title: Quarantine workers face 6 months prison
item.description: Frontline workers in Queensland’s hotel quarantine who do not get tested for COVID-19 every week face up to six months in prison or a $13,000 fine.

item.title: ‘Abhorrent’: Fears of all-out bikie war
item.description: A Rebels bikie member has described the killing of his gang’s former president Nick Martin as “absolutely abhorrent”, sparking fears Saturday night’s shooting could lead to an all-out bikie war.

item.title: Tributes for dog walker killed at servo
item.description: A community is mourning the death of a rugby league club volunteer and “larrikin” who was allegedly stabbed to death while out walking his daughter’s dog.

item.title: Secret to great NAPLAN results
item.description: Schools that improve their performance in NAPLAN tests tend to tailor teaching to the needs of different students, a new analysis has found.

item.title: Funding boost to keep Aussie airlines alive
item.description: Aussie airlines will get extra help from taxpayers ahead of the Christmas period to help keep people connected, the federal government has announced.

item.title: Duo hospitalised, stabbed in home attack
item.description: Two people have been hospitalised after a NSW man allegedly attacked them with a kitchen knife.

item.title: Road rage video shows violent attack
item.description: Footage of a road rage incident has emerged where a man alleged punched the window of another vehicle.
